15 WHEREAS, in 2024, the program was revived and renamed the Scott Riner Prison
16 Awareness Program to honor his lasting impact and his commitment to youth in Gwinnett
17 County; and
18 WHEREAS, Officer Riner led an exceptional career of public service and his inspiring
19 commitment to the welfare of others stands as a shining example of the positive effect law
20 enforcement professionals have on the lives and well-being of others; and
21 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Officer Riner will long be remembered for
22 his love of family and friendship, and this dedicated law enforcement officer will be missed
23 by all who had the great fortune of knowing him; and
24 WHEREAS, Officer Riner exhibited extraordinary devotion to public service, outstanding
25 loyalty, fine leadership, and meticulous attention to detail in all of his duties and it is
26 abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable and distinguished Georgian be recognized
27 appropriately by dedicating an intersection in his memory.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
29 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the intersection of State Route 316 and Hi Hope Road in
30 Gwinnett County is dedicated as the Officer Scott Riner Memorial Intersection.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation is authorized and
32 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs dedicating the Officer Scott Riner Memorial
33 Intersection.
